claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: The image shows the title page of an original article titled 'Recombinant or Standard-Dose Influenza Vaccine in Adults under 65 Years of Age,' listing authors and beginning the abstract text describing antigen content of trivalent recombinant vs. egg-based vaccines. This page contains only the article title, author list, and introductory abstract text; it does not provide any information about Flublok’s antigenic match to WHO- or FDA-selected strains and therefore does not support the claim. Note: Limited to the visible title and abstract excerpt; no data on antigenic match is shown
